OL,3,CAlcohol deaths drop by more than 20%
OL,4,Cin Dumfries and Galloway
OL,6,F"It is welcome to see the number of
OL,7,Fdeaths at the lowest level since 2019
OL,8,Fand we are continuing to work closely
OL,9,Fwith local Alcohol and Drugs
OL,10,FPartnerships (ADPs) and other
OL,11,Fstakeholders to provide targeted,
OL,12,Fperson-centred support, backed by
OL,13,Frecord levels of funding of around
OL,14,F#160 million this year.
OL,16,F"However, while we are making progress
OL,17,Fon tackling the harms caused by
OL,18,Falcohol, we cannot become complacent.
